<p><b>Paul Frederic Simon</b> (born October 13, 1941) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Singer-songwriter" title="Singer-songwriter" class="mw-redirect">singer-songwriter</a> and <a href="/wiki/Musician" title="Musician">musician</a>, perhaps best known for his partnership with <a href="/wiki/Art_Garfunkel" title="Art Garfunkel">Art Garfunkel</a> in the duo <a href="/wiki/Simon_%26_Garfunkel" title="Simon &amp; Garfunkel">Simon &amp; Garfunkel</a>. In 2006, <i><a href="/wiki/Time_(magazine)" title="Time (magazine)">Time</a></i> magazine called him one of the 100 "people who shape our world."<sup id="cite_ref-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> As of 2007, he resides in <a href="/wiki/New_Canaan,_Connecticut" title="New Canaan, Connecticut">New Canaan, Connecticut</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
